processed.result:
You are given a short program written in a simple language. The language has four commands:

*  "H" prints "Hello, World!"
*  "Q" prints the program itself
*  "9" prints the lyrics to the song "99 Bottles of Beer"
*  "+" increases a counter

Any other characters are ignored.

Determine if running this program will produce any output. 


Input: A single line containing the program.

Output: "YES" if the program will print something, "NO" otherwise.

Determine if a given sequence of characters, representing a simple program, will produce any output. The program uses four specific commands: "H" (prints a fixed phrase), "Q" (prints the program itself), "9" (prints a song), and "+" (increments a counter).
